OSOGBO – Osun State Governor Adegboyega Oyetola has cast his vote at his unit 2, ward 1, LA Primary School, Popo Iragbiji, Osun State. He advocated for an increase in the number of the Bimodal Voter Accreditation System (BVAS) machines in each unit to make the process of voting faster. He spoke with newsmen shortly after casting his vote at his unit. According to him, “considering the time frame we have for voting, they need to speed up or increase the number of machines so as to ensure that the process is completed within the time frame. While commending the security agents for being alive to their responsibility, Oyetola noted that they have creditably well. ” Seeing the enthusiasm that voters have displayed to cast their votes, I’m particularly very grateful to them and that shows that people are conscious of the need to participate in the process. Once the process is transparent enough, people will not be persuaded to vote, there will be no voters apathy. Oyetola also expressed confident that he will be reelected by the grace of Almighty God.